hands_on_practices.solution:
1. Substitution.  Let 
$$y(x)=-1+\frac1{v(x)}\,,\quad \frac{dy}{dx}=-\frac{v'}{v^2}\,. $$
2. Rewrite the Riccati equation 
$$\frac{dy}{dx}=x-xy^2
\;\Longrightarrow\;
-\frac{v'}{v^2}=x - x\Bigl(-1+\frac1v\Bigr)^2
= x - x\Bigl(1-\frac{2}{v}+\frac1{v^2}\Bigr)
=\frac{2x}{v}-\frac{x}{v^2}\,. $$
Multiply by $v^2$:
$$-v'=2xv - x
\;\Longrightarrow\;
v'+2xv=x\,. $$
3. Solve the linear ODE.  The integrating factor is 
$$\mu(x)=e^{\int2x\,dx}=e^{x^2}\,. $$
Multiply by $\mu$:
$$\frac{d}{dx}\bigl(v e^{x^2}\bigr)=x e^{x^2}
\;\Longrightarrow\;
v e^{x^2}
=\int x e^{x^2}\,dx
=\tfrac12e^{x^2}+C
\;\Longrightarrow\;
v=\tfrac12+Ce^{-x^2}\,. $$
4. Apply $y(0)=0$.  Then $0=-1+1/v(0)$ gives $v(0)=1$, so 
$$1=\tfrac12+C\quad\Rightarrow\quad C=\tfrac12
\;\Longrightarrow\;
v=\frac{1+e^{-x^2}}{2}\,. $$
Hence
$$y(x)=-1+\frac{2}{1+e^{-x^2}}
=\frac{1-e^{-x^2}}{1+e^{-x^2}}
=\tanh\!\bigl(\tfrac{x^2}{2}\bigr)\,. $$
5. Evaluate at $x_0=\sqrt{\ln3}$:
$$y(\sqrt{\ln3})
=\frac{1-e^{-\ln3}}{1+e^{-\ln3}}
=\frac{1-\frac13}{1+\frac13}
=\frac{2/3}{4/3}
=\tfrac12\,. $$
